  "prompt": "How do I keep Instagram private from Facebook friends and contacts?",
  "response": "To keep your Instagram private from Facebook friends and contacts:\n\n1. Adjust Instagram Privacy Settings:\n- Go to your Instagram profile\n- Tap the menu icon\n- Select \"Settings\"\n- Choose \"Privacy\"\n- Set your account to \"Private\"\n\n2. Control Facebook Connections:\n- In Instagram Settings, go to \"Linked Accounts\"\n- Disconnect or unlink your Facebook account\n\n3. Manage Contact Syncing:\n- In Instagram Settings, go to \"Contacts\"\n- Turn off \"Allow Access\" for phone contacts and Facebook contacts\n\n4. Additional Privacy Tips:\n- Don't use your Facebook friends list to find Instagram friends\n- Be selective about who you accept follow requests\n- Use a different email/phone number for Instagram than Facebook\n\n5. Optional: Create a Separate Profile\n- Consider creating a new Instagram account with different contact information\n\nThese steps will help limit who can see your Instagram content from your Facebook network.",
